Shortest paths were computed for the individual response networks by considering all nodes, using the Dijkstra’s algorithm, implemented in python. The algorithm computes minimum weight shortest paths, in which each path begins from a source node and ends with a sink node, through interacting proteins, choosing the least-cost edge in every step. The rationale For a path of length n in condition A, the path cost was computed as a summation of the edge weights constituting the path. The resultant shortest paths were ranked-based on their path cost using a percentile approach, with paths having a lower path cost given a higher rank.4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
